==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pentane
<hw>Pen"tane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Penta-</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one of the three
metameric hydrocarbons, <chform>C5H12</chform>, of the methane or
paraffin series. They are colorless, volatile liquids, two of which
occur in petroleum. So called because of the <xex>five</xex> carbon
atoms in the molecule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pentangle</ent>⟦br⟧
